          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1633431138426-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1633431138426-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1633431138426-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the basa is golden, transfer it to a plate and set aside for later</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Carefully pour away most of the oil and return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> and<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633431152235-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633431152235-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633431152235-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633431152235-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633431152235-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>honey</strong> <strong>sauce</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until thick and sticky</p><p>Once the sauce has thickened, return the <strong>golden basa</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for 1-2 min further or until the basa is fully coated – this is your <strong>General Tso's basa</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1633431186482-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1633431186482-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1633431186482-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1633431186482-x1000.jpg",
